<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE 98/49/EC of 29 June 1998 on safeguarding the supplementary pension rights of employed and self-employed persons moving within the Community </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 98/49/E&Uuml; &uuml;henduse piires liikuvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjate t&auml;iendavate pensioni&otilde;iguste kaitse kohta 29. juuni 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Articles 51 and 235 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikleid 51 ja 235, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas one of the fundamental freedoms of the Community is the free movement of persons; whereas the Treaty provides that the Council shall, acting unanimously, adopt such measures in the field of social security as are necessary to provide freedom of movement of workers; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) &uuml;ks &uuml;henduse p&otilde;hivabadus on isikute vaba liikumine; asutamislepinguga n&auml;hakse ette, et n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;tab sotsiaalkindlustuse valdkonnas &uuml;heh&auml;&auml;lselt vastu meetmed, mis on vajalikud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate liikumisvabaduse tagamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas the social protection of workers is ensured by statutory social security schemes complemented by supplementary social security schemes; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate sotsiaalne kaitse tagatakse riiklike sotsiaalkindlustusskeemidega ja t&auml;iendavate sotsiaalkindlustusskeemidega; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas the legislation already adopted by the Council with a view to protecting the social security rights of workers moving within the Community and of members of their family, namely Council Regulations (EEC) No 1408/71 of 14 June 1971 on the application of social security schemes to employed persons, to self-employed persons and to members of their families moving within the Community (4) and (EEC) No 574/72 of 21 March 1972 laying down the procedure for implementing Regulation (EEC) No 1408/71 on the application of social security schemes to employed persons, to self-employed persons and to members of their families moving within the Community (5), concern only statutory pension schemes; whereas the system of coordination provided for in those Regulations does not extend to supplementary pension schemes, except for schemes which are covered by the term 'legislation' as defined by the first subparagraph of Article 1(j) of Regulation (EEC) No 1408/71 or in respect of which a Member State makes a declaration under that Article; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) &otilde;igusaktid, mis n&otilde;ukogu on &uuml;henduse piires liikuvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja nende pereliikmete sotsiaalkindlustus&otilde;iguste kaitseks juba vastu v&otilde;tnud, nimelt n&otilde;ukogu 14. juuni 1971. aasta m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 (sotsiaalkindlustusskeemide kohaldamise kohta &uuml;henduse piires liikuvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate, f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjate ja nende pereliikmete suhtes) (4) ja n&otilde;ukogu 21. m&auml;rtsi 1972. aasta m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 574/72, millega n&auml;hakse ette m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 (sotsiaalkindlustusskeemide kohaldamise kohta &uuml;henduse piires liikuvate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate, f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjate ja nende pereliikmete suhtes) rakendamise kord, (5) k&auml;sitlevad ainult riiklikke pensioniskeeme; nende m&auml;&auml;rustega etten&auml;htud koosk&otilde;lastuss&uuml;steem ei laiene t&auml;iendavatele pensioniskeemidele, v&auml;lja arvatud skeemid, mida h&otilde;lmab m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 artikli 1 punkti j esimeses l&otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;ratletud m&otilde;iste "&otilde;igusaktid" v&otilde;i mille suhtes liikmesriik teeb k&otilde;nealuse artikli alusel avalduse; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas the Council has a wide discretion regarding the choice of the most appropriate measures for attaining the objective of Article 51 of the Treaty; and whereas the system of coordination provided for in Regulations (EEC) No 1408/71 and (EEC) No 574/72, and in particular the rules of aggregation, are not appropriate to supplementary pension schemes, except for schemes which are covered by the term 'legislation' as defined by the first subparagraph of Article 1(j) of Regulation (EEC) No 1408/71 or in respect of which a Member State makes a declaration under that Article, and should therefore be subject to specific measures, of which this Directive is the first, in order to take account of their special nature and characteristics and the diversity of such schemes within and between Member States; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) n&otilde;ukogul on asutamislepingu artiklis 51 s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks sobivaimate meetmete valimiseks laialdased volitused; m&auml;&auml;rustega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 ja (EM&Uuml;) nr 574/72 etten&auml;htud koosk&otilde;latuss&uuml;steemi, eriti liitmist k&auml;sitlevaid eeskirju, ei sobi kohaldada t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemide suhtes, v&auml;lja arvatud skeemid, mida h&otilde;lmab m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 artikli 1 punkti j esimeses l&otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;ratletud m&otilde;iste "&otilde;igusaktid" v&otilde;i mille suhtes liikmesriik teeb k&otilde;nealuse artikli alusel avalduse, seep&auml;rast tuleks nende suhtes kohaldada erimeetmeid, millest k&auml;esolev direktiiv on esimene, eesm&auml;rgiga v&otilde;tta arvesse selliste skeemide erip&auml;ra ja -jooni ning nende erinevusi liikmesriikide vahel ja liikmesriikides; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas no pension or benefit should be subject to both the provisions of this Directive and those of Regulations (EEC) No 1408/71 and (EEC) No 574/72, and therefore any supplementary pension scheme which comes within the scope of those Regulations, because a Member State has made a declaration to that effect under Article 1(j) of Regulation (EEC) No 1408/71, cannot be subject to the provisions of this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) &uuml;hegi pensioni ega h&uuml;vitise suhtes ei v&otilde;i kohalda korraga nii k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kui ka m&auml;&auml;ruste (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 ja (EM&Uuml;) nr 574/72 s&auml;tteid, seep&auml;rast ei saa &uuml;hegi t&auml;iendava pensioniskeemi suhtes, mis kuulub k&otilde;nealuste m&auml;&auml;ruste reguleerimisalasse, sest et liikmesriik on nende kohta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 artikli 1 punkti j alusel teinud avalduse, kohaldada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas in its Recommendation 92/442/EEC of 27 July 1992 on the convergence of social protection objectives and policies (6) the Council recommended that Member States should 'promote, where necessary, changes to the conditions governing the acquisition of pension and, especially, supplementary pension rights with a view to eliminating obstacles to the mobility of employed workers'; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) 27. juuli 1992. aasta soovituses 92/442/EM&Uuml; sotsiaalse kaitse eesm&auml;rkide ja poliitika l&auml;hendamise kohta (6) soovitas n&otilde;ukogu liikmesriikidel "soodustada vajaduse korral vanaduspensioni ja eriti t&auml;iendava pensioni saamise tingimuste muutmist, et k&otilde;rvaldada t&ouml;&ouml;tajate liikumise takistused"; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas a contribution to this objective can be made if workers who move or whose place of employment moves from one Member State to another are guaranteed equal treatment as regards the protection of their supplementary pension rights with workers who remain or whose place of employment changes but remains within the same Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) sellele eesm&auml;rgile saab kaasa aidata, kui t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele, kes liiguvad v&otilde;i kelle t&ouml;&ouml;koht liigub &uuml;hest liikmesriigist teise, tagatakse t&auml;iendavate pensioni&otilde;iguste osas v&otilde;rdne kohtlemine nende t&ouml;&ouml;tajatega, kes j&auml;&auml;vad samasse liikmesriiki elama v&otilde;i kelle t&ouml;&ouml;koht muutub, kuid j&auml;&auml;b samasse liikmesriiki; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas freedom of movement for persons, which is one of the basic rights enshrined in the Treaty, is not confined to employed persons but also extends to self-employed persons; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) isikute liikumisvabadus, mis on &uuml;ks asutamislepingus nimetatud p&otilde;hi&otilde;igusi, ei puuduta ainult t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid, vaid ka f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjaid; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the Treaty does not provide powers other than those of Article 235 to take appropriate measures within the field of social security for self-employed persons; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) asutamislepingus ei n&auml;hta f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjate sotsiaalkindlustuse valdkonnas asjakohaste meetmete v&otilde;tmiseks ette muid volitusi peale artiklis 235 s&auml;testatute; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas, in order to enable the right of free movement to be exercised effectively, workers and others holding entitlement should have certain guarantees for equal treatment regarding the preservation of their vested pension rights deriving from supplementary pension schemes; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) vaba liikumise &otilde;iguse tulemuslikuks kasutamiseks peaksid t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel ja teistel k&otilde;nealust &otilde;igust valdavatel isikutel olema teatavad tagatised v&otilde;rdseks kohtlemiseks t&auml;iendavatest pensioniskeemidest tulenevate pensioni&otilde;iguste s&auml;ilimise suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Whereas the Member States should take the necessary measures to ensure that benefits under supplementary pension schemes are paid to members and former members thereof as well as others holding entitlement under such schemes in all Member States, given that all restrictions on the free movement of payments and capital are prohibited under Article 73b of the Treaty; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) liikmesriigid peaksid v&otilde;tma vajalikke meetmeid selle tagamiseks, et t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemide kohast h&uuml;vitist makstakse nende skeemidega h&otilde;lmatud v&otilde;i varem h&otilde;lmatud isikutele, samuti teistele k&otilde;nealuste skeemide kohaselt sellist &otilde;igust valdavatele isikutele k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides, tingimusel et asutamislepingu artikli 73b alusel on keelatud k&otilde;ik piirangud maksete ja kapitali vabale liikumisele; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Whereas in order to facilitate the exercise of the right to free movement, national regulations should, where necessary, be adjusted in order to enable contributions to continue to be made to a supplementary pension scheme established in one Member State by or on behalf of workers who are posted to another Member State in accordance with Title II of Regulation (EEC) No 1408/71; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) vaba liikumise &otilde;iguse kasutamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks peaks siseriiklikke &otilde;igusakte vajaduse korral kohandama, et vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 II jaotisele teise liikmesriiki t&ouml;&ouml;le l&auml;hetatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel v&otilde;i nende nimel oleks v&otilde;imalik j&auml;tkata sissemaksete tegemist m&otilde;nes teises liikmesriigis koostatud t&auml;iendavasse pensioniskeemi; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Whereas in this regard the Treaty requires not only the abolition of any discrimination based on nationality between workers of the Member States but also the elimination of any national measure likely to impede or render less attractive for those workers the exercise of the fundamental freedoms guaranteed by the Treaty as interpreted by the Court of Justice of the European Communities in successive judgments; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) selles suhtes ei n&otilde;uta asutamislepinguga mitte ainult liikmesriikide t&ouml;&ouml;tajate kodakondsusel p&otilde;hineva diskrimineerimise kaotamist, vaid loobumist ka k&otilde;ikidest sellistest siseriiklikest meetmetest, mis v&otilde;iksid t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt takistada asutamislepinguga tagatud ja hilisemate Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Kohtu otsuste kohaselt t&otilde;lgendatud p&otilde;hivabaduste kasutamist v&otilde;i v&auml;hendada huvi nende kasutamise vastu; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) Whereas workers exercising their right to free movement should be adequately informed by employers, trustees or others responsible for the management of supplementary pension schemes, particularly with regard to the choices and alternatives available to them; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) t&ouml;&ouml;andjad, usaldusisikud v&otilde;i teised t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemide haldamise eest vastutavad isikud peaksid vaba liikumise &otilde;igust kasutavaid t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid asjakohaselt teavitama, eelk&otilde;ige nendele k&auml;ttesaadavatest valikutest ja v&otilde;imalustest; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Whereas this Directive is without prejudice to the laws of the Member States concerning collective action to defend the interests of trades and professions; </inglise>
<eesti> 15) k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei piira nende liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide kohaldamist, mis k&auml;sitlevad kollektiivmeetmeid ameti- ja erialaste huvide kaitseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Whereas, by reason of the diversity of supplementary social security schemes, the Community should lay down only a general framework of objectives and therefore a Directive is the appropriate legal instrument; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemide erinevuse t&otilde;ttu peaks &uuml;hendus ette n&auml;gema ainult eesm&auml;rkide &uuml;ldraamistiku ja direktiiv on selleks sobivaim &otilde;igusakt; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) Whereas, in accordance with the principles of subsidiarity and proportionality as set out in Article 3b of the Treaty, the objectives of this Directive cannot be sufficiently achieved by the Member States and can therefore be better achieved by the Community; whereas this Directive does not go beyond what is necessary to achieve those objectives, </inglise>
<eesti> 17) asutamislepingu artiklis 3b s&auml;testatud subsidiaarsus- ja proportsionaalsusp&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaselt ei suuda liikmesriigid t&auml;ielikult saavutada k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rke ning seet&otilde;ttu v&otilde;ib neid paremini saavutada &uuml;henduse tasandil; k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei l&auml;he nimetatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks vajalikust kaugemale, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER I </inglise>
<eesti> I PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> OBJECTIVE AND SCOPE </inglise>
<eesti> EESM&Auml;RK JA REGULEERIMISALA </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The aim of this Directive is to protect the rights of members of supplementary pension schemes who move from one Member State to another, thereby contributing to the removal of obstacles to the free movement of employed and self-employed persons within the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on kaitsta &uuml;hest liikmesriigist teise liikuvate t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemidega h&otilde;lmatud isikute &otilde;igusi, aidates k&otilde;rvaldada takistusi, mis piiravad t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjate vaba liikumist &uuml;henduse piires. </eesti>
<inglise> Such protection refers to pension rights under both voluntary and compulsory supplementary pension schemes, with the exception of schemes covered by Regulation (EEC) No 1408/71. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealune kaitse k&auml;sitleb nii vabatahtliku kui ka kohustusliku t&auml;iendava pensioniskeemi kohaseid pensioni&otilde;igusi, v&auml;lja arvatud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 h&otilde;lmatud skeemid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall apply to members of supplementary pension schemes and others holding entitlement under such schemes who have acquired or are in the process of acquiring rights in one or more Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemidega h&otilde;lmatud isikute ja teiste k&otilde;nealuste skeemide kohaseid &otilde;igusi valdavate isikute suhtes, kes on omandanud v&otilde;i parajasti omandavad &otilde;igusi &uuml;hes v&otilde;i mitmes liikmesriigis. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER II </inglise>
<eesti> II peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise> DEFINITIONS </inglise>
<eesti> M&Otilde;ISTED </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) 'supplementary pension' means retirement pensions and, where provided for by the rules of a supplementary pension scheme established in conformity with national legislation and practice, invalidity and survivors' benefits, intended to supplement or replace those provided in respect of the same contingencies by statutory social security schemes; </inglise>
<eesti> a) t&auml;iendav pension - vanaduspensionid ja, kui see on ette n&auml;htud siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide ja tavade kohaselt koostatud t&auml;iendava pensioniskeemi eeskirjadega, t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus- v&otilde;i toitjakaotush&uuml;vitised, mille eesm&auml;rk on t&auml;iendada v&otilde;i asendada samade juhtumite suhtes riiklike sotsiaalkindlustusskeemidega etten&auml;htud h&uuml;vitisi; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) 'supplementary pension scheme' means any occupational pension scheme established in conformity with national legislation and practice such as a group insurance contract or pay-as-you-go scheme agreed by one or more branches or sectors, funded scheme or pension promise backed by book reserves, or any collective or other comparable arrangement intended to provide a supplementary pension for employed or self-employed persons; </inglise>
<eesti> b) t&auml;iendav pensioniskeem - siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide ja tavade kohaselt koostatud kutsealane pensioniskeem, nagu n&auml;iteks grupikindlustusleping v&otilde;i &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme valdkonna raames kokkulepitud p&otilde;lvkondadevaheline &uuml;mberjaotusskeem, kogumisskeem v&otilde;i pensionilubadus eelarve reservist v&otilde;i m&otilde;ni v&otilde;rreldav kollektiivne v&otilde;i muu skeem t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjatele t&auml;iendava pensioni kindlustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) 'pension rights' means any benefits to which scheme members and others holding entitlement are entitled under the rules of a supplementary pension scheme and, where applicable, under national legislation; </inglise>
<eesti> c) pensioni&otilde;igus - h&uuml;vitised, millele t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemidega h&otilde;lmatud isikutel ja teiste k&otilde;nealuste skeemide kohaseid &otilde;igusi valdavatel isikutel on &otilde;igus vastavalt t&auml;iendava pensioniskeemi eeskirjadele ja vajaduse korral siseriiklikele &otilde;igusaktidele; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) 'vested pension rights' means any entitlement to benefits obtained after fulfilment of the conditions required by the rules of a supplementary pension scheme and, where applicable, under national legislation; </inglise>
<eesti> d) omandatud pensioni&otilde;igused - &otilde;igus h&uuml;vitistele, mis on omandatud p&auml;rast t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemide eeskirjade ja vajaduse korral siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt n&otilde;utavate tingimuste t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) 'posted worker' means a person who is posted to work in another Member State and who under the terms of Title II of Regulation (EEC) No 1408/71 continues to be subject to the legislation of the Member State of origin, and 'posting' shall be construed accordingly; </inglise>
<eesti> e) l&auml;hetatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja - isik, kes on saadetud t&ouml;&ouml;le teise liikmesriiki ja kelle suhtes kohaldatakse vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1408/71 II jaotisele j&auml;tkuvalt p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi &otilde;igusakte; m&otilde;istet l&auml;hetamine t&otilde;lgendatakse vastavalt sellele; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) 'contribution' means any payment made or deemed to have been made to a supplementary pension scheme. </inglise>
<eesti> f) sissemakse - t&auml;iendavasse pensioniskeemi tehtud v&otilde;i tehtuks loetud makse. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER III </inglise>
<eesti> III PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> MEASURES FOR SAFEGUARDING THE SUPPLEMENTARY PENSION RIGHTS OF WORKERS MOVING WITHIN THE COMMUNITY </inglise>
<eesti> MEETMED &Uuml;HENDUSE PIIRES LIIKUVATE T&Ouml;&Ouml;TAJATE T&Auml;IENDAVATE PENSIONI&Otilde;IGUSTE KAITSEKS </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Equality of treatment as regards preservation of pension rights </inglise>
<eesti> V&otilde;rdne kohtlemine pensioni&otilde;iguste s&auml;ilimise suhtes </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take the necessary measures to ensure the preservation of vested pension rights for members of a supplementary pension scheme in respect of whom contributions are no longer being made to that scheme as a consequence of their moving from one Member State to another, to the same extent as for members in respect of whom contributions are no longer being made but who remain within the same Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vajalikke meetmeid, et tagada omandatud pensioni&otilde;iguste s&auml;ilimine t&auml;iendava pensioniskeemiga h&otilde;lmatud isikutele, kelle puhul nende &uuml;hest liikmesriigist teise liikumise t&otilde;ttu ei tehta enam k&otilde;nealusesse kavasse sissemakseid, samas ulatuses kui nende skeemidega h&otilde;lmatud isikutele, kelle puhul sissemakseid enam ei tehta, kuid kes j&auml;&auml;vad samasse liikmesriiki. </eesti>
<inglise> This Article shall also apply to other persons holding entitlement under the rules of the supplementary pension scheme in question. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat artiklit kohaldatakse ka teiste k&otilde;nealuse t&auml;iendava pensioniskeemi eeskirjade kohaseid &otilde;igusi valdavate isikute suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Cross border payments </inglise>
<eesti> V&auml;lismaksed </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that, in respect of members of supplementary pension schemes, as well as others holding entitlement under such schemes, supplementary pension schemes make payment in other Member States, net of any taxes and transaction charges which may be applicable, of all benefits due under such schemes. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et t&auml;iendavatest pensioniskeemidest makstakse t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemidega h&otilde;lmatud isikutele ja teistele k&otilde;nealuste skeemide kohaseid &otilde;igusi valdavatele isikutele teistes liikmesriikides k&otilde;ik k&otilde;nealuste skeemide kohased h&uuml;vitised, ilma maksude ja tehingutasudeta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Contributions to supplementary pension schemes by and on behalf of posted workers </inglise>
<eesti> L&auml;hetatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajate poolt v&otilde;i nimel tehtud sissemaksed t&auml;iendavatesse pensioniskeemidesse </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall adopt such measures as are necessary to enable contributions to continue to be made to a supplementary pension scheme established in a Member State by or on behalf of a posted worker who is a member of such a scheme during the period of his or her posting in another Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad vastu vajalikud meetmed, et liikmesriigis koostatud t&auml;iendavasse pensioniskeemi sissemaksete tegemist skeemiga h&otilde;lmatud l&auml;hetatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja poolt v&otilde;i nimel oleks v&otilde;imalik j&auml;tkata ajal, kui ta on saadetud teise liikmesriiki. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Where, pursuant to paragraph 1, contributions continue to be made to a supplementary pension scheme in one Member State, the posted worker and, where applicable, his employer shall be exempted from any obligation to make contributions to a supplementary pension scheme in another Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui vastavalt l&otilde;ikele 1 j&auml;tkatakse sissemaksete tegemist t&auml;iendavasse pensioniskeemi &uuml;hes liikmesriigis, vabastatakse l&auml;hetatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja vajaduse korral tema t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustusest teha sissemakseid teise riigi t&auml;iendavasse pensioniskeemi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Information to scheme members </inglise>
<eesti> Teave skeemiga h&otilde;lmatud isikutele </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take measures to ensure that employers, trustees or others responsible for the management of supplementary pension schemes provide adequate information to scheme members, when they move to another Member State, as to their pension rights and the choices which are available to them under the scheme. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad meetmeid selle tagamiseks, et t&ouml;&ouml;andjad, usaldusisikud v&otilde;i teised t&auml;iendavate pensioniskeemide haldamise eest vastutavad isikud teavitaksid skeemiga h&otilde;lmatud isikuid nende teise liikmesriiki suundumise korral piisavalt nende pensioni&otilde;igustest ja k&otilde;nealuse skeemi kohaselt nende k&auml;sutuses olevatest valikutest. </eesti>
<inglise> Such information shall at least correspond to information given to scheme members in respect of whom contributions cease to be made but who remain within the same Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Selline teave peab v&auml;hemalt vastama teabele, mida jagatakse nendele kavaga h&otilde;lmatud isikutele, kelle suhtes sissemaksete tegemine l&otilde;petatakse, kuid kes j&auml;&auml;vad samasse liikmesriiki. </eesti>
<inglise> CHAPTER IV </inglise>
<eesti> IV PEAT&Uuml;KK </eesti>
<inglise> FINAL PROVISIONS </inglise>
<eesti> L&Otilde;PPS&Auml;TTED </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may provide that the provisions of Article 6 shall apply only to postings that commence on or after 25 July 2001. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad ette n&auml;ha, et artiklit 6 kohaldatakse ainult selliste l&auml;hetuste suhtes, mis algavad 25. juulil 2001 v&otilde;i p&auml;rast seda kuup&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall introduce into their national legal systems such measures as are necessary to enable all persons who consider themselves wronged by failure to apply the provisions of this Directive to pursue their claims by judicial process after possible recourse to other competent authorities. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad oma siseriiklikes &otilde;iguss&uuml;steemides meetmed v&otilde;imaldamaks isikutel, kes leiavad, et neid on k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tete eiramise t&otilde;ttu &otilde;igusvastaselt koheldud, taotleda oma &otilde;iguste kaitset kohtu kaudu, olles vastava v&otilde;imaluse korral esmalt p&ouml;&ouml;rdunud p&auml;devate asutuste poole. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall bring into force the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary to comply with this Directive not later than 36 months following the date of its entry into force, or shall ensure by that date at the latest that management and labour introduce the requisite provisions by way of agreement. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud &otilde;igusnormid hiljemalt 36 kuu jooksul alates direktiivi j&otilde;ustumisest v&otilde;i tagavad hiljemalt selleks t&auml;htajaks, et t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooled kehtestavad n&otilde;utavad s&auml;tted kokkuleppe teel. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take all necessary steps to enable themselves at all times to guarantee the results imposed by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad k&otilde;ik vajalikud abin&otilde;ud, et v&otilde;imaldada neil igal ajal tagada k&auml;esolevas direktiivis etten&auml;htud tulemuste saavutamine. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall immediately inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Nad teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> When Member States adopt these provisions, these shall contain a reference to this Directive or shall be accompanied by such reference at the time of their official publication. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid k&otilde;nealused normid vastu v&otilde;tavad, lisavad nad nendesse v&otilde;i nende ametliku avaldamise korral nende juurde viite k&auml;esolevale direktiivile. </eesti>
<inglise> The procedure for such reference shall be adopted by Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellise viitamise viisi n&auml;evad ette liikmesriigid. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall inform the Commission of the national authorities to be contacted regarding the application of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad komisjonile asutuste nimed, kelle poole k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamise k&uuml;simustes p&ouml;&ouml;rduda. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Not later than 25 January 2002 Member States shall communicate to the Commission the text of the provisions of national law which they adopt in the field covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas nende poolt vastuv&otilde;etavate siseriiklike &otilde;igusnormide teksti hiljemalt 25. jaanuariks 2002. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> On the basis of the information supplied by Member States, the Commission shall submit a report to the European Parliament, the Council and the Economic and Social Committee, within six years of the entry into force of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide edastatud teabe p&otilde;hjal esitab komisjon Euroopa Parlamendile, n&otilde;ukogule ning majandus- ja sotsiaalkomiteele aruande kuue aasta jooksul alates k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&otilde;ustumisest. </eesti>
<inglise> The report shall deal with the application of this Directive and shall, where appropriate, propose any amendments that may prove necessary. </inglise>
<eesti> Aruanne k&auml;sitleb k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kohaldamist ja vajaduse korral teeb komisjon muudatusettepanekuid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> Direktiiv j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
